26/10/2006
BITOLA, Macedonia -- Croatian President Stipe Mesic formally opened a Croatian consular office Wednesday (October 25th) in Bitola, as he wrapped up a three-day visit to Macedonia. 
Branko Maretic, a Croat who has been living and working for years in Bitola, will head the office. 
It is expected to strengthen cultural and economic ties between the two states.
Also Wednesday, Mesic held an informal meeting with Kosovo Prime Minister Agim Ceku in Skopje. 
Mesic said Ceku briefed him on the latest developments in the Kosovo status negotiations and proposed a direct air link between Pristina and Zagreb. 
(Vjesnik, Vecer - 26/10/06; A1 TV, Makfax - 25/10/06)
